<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="871" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/263</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Danish Minister</gloss> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Danish Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-22">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I hasten to
                                inform you that I have just now (2.35 p.m.) received a cablegram
                                from the Danish Minister of Foreign Affairs advising me that the
                                Treaty for the cession of the Danish West India Islands has been
                                passed by the Danish Parliament and ratified by His Majesty the
                                King, and that the Danish instrument of ratification with full power
                                for me to exchange will be sent to me by Swedish steamer from
                                Gothenburg on the 30th instant.</p>
                            <p>I know this information will be gratifying to you, and I remain
                                [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">C. Brun</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>